Description of problem: crash

Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.7.1 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/lib64/firefox/firefox crash_function: AsmJSFaultHandler(int, siginfo_t*, void*) executable: /usr/lib64/firefox/firefox global_pid: 3266 kernel: 4.5.7-300.fc24.x86_64 pkg_vendor: (none) reproducible: Not sure how to reproduce the problem runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 500

This is a private, duplicate bug report of bug 1348344. The report has been created because Bugzilla cannot grant access to a comment for a specific group.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 1348344 ***
Reproduction steps: - Download firefox from https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/stransky/firefox-wayland/ - Launch from side menu bar - crash (ABRT catches it) - launches fine from terminal
*** Bug 1348344 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
Fixed by disabling start-up notifications on -8.wayland package.

Similar problem has been detected:
Browsed to maps.google.com (on Fedora 24 running in a VMware virtual machine). Note that the same excersize on a pre-upgraded Fedora 23 caused a VMware Workstation crash.
